Package: RegCalib
Title: Regression Calibration for Measurement Error Correction
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Wenze", "Tang", role = c("aut")),
    person("Molin", "Wang", role = c("aut")),
    person("Jingyu", "Cui", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "jingyu.cui@yale.edu"))
Description: Corrects for measurement error in continuous exposures (and
    covariates) using regression calibration methods. Provides corrected
    coefficients, standard errors, p-values, and variance-covariance
    matrices for linear, generalized linear, and Cox proportional hazards
    outcome models under both external and internal validation study designs.
    Implements the diattenuation factor method
    (RegCalibDF) and the substitution approach (RegCalibSub). Supports single and multiple
    mismeasured exposures.
